    "body": "why not use something like [direnv](https://github.com/direnv/direnv)\r\n\r\ndirenv is not loading the `.envrc` into the current shell. It's creating a new bash sub-process to load the stdlib (, direnvrc and .envrc, and only exports the environment diff back to the original shell. This allows direnv to record the environment changes accurately and also work with all sorts of shells and load whatever configuration \r\n\r\nanother alternative maybe using something like [Justfile](https://github.com/casey/just#dotenv-integration). ",
